articles.author: Stephen Collinson and Sara Murray, CNN
articles.title: Obamacare repeal bill a test for dealmaker-in-chief
articles.description: President Trump is wading into the fray Thursday and flexing his deal making skills to build momentum behind the Republican Party's Obamacare repeal bill

articles.title: Barton: 'I will buy Waffle House for everyone' if you speed things up - CNN Video
articles.description: Rep. Joe Barton offered to treat all members of the House Energy and Commerce committee to a breakfast at Waffle House if they speed up a session on the GOP's Obamacare replacement bill.

articles.author: Jim Acosta, CNN
articles.title: Trump to conservative leaders: If this plan fails, I'll blame Democrats
articles.description: In an Oval Office meeting featuring leaders of conservative groups that already lining up against House Republicans' plan to repeal and replace Obamacare, President Donald Trump revealed his plan in the event the GOP effort doesn't succeed: Allow Obamacare to fail and let Democrats take the blame, sources at the gathering told CNN.

articles.author: Daniella Diaz and Amanda Wills, CNN
articles.title: President Trump today: Live updates
articles.description: The GOP released their Obamacare replacement plan, and President Trump is selling it hard. Here are the latest updates.

articles.author: Tami Luhby
articles.title: Who wins and who loses in Republicans' plan to repeal and replace Obamacare
articles.description: Many people could lose coverage under the Republicans' plan to repeal and replace Obamacare. Younger, healthier people who want skimpier plans would likely benefit, but older sicker consumers could pay more.

articles.author: Jennifer Agiesta, CNN Polling Director
articles.title: CNN/ORC poll: Most want compromise in DC
articles.description: Americans are spending a lot of time talking politics these days, and one clear consensus amid the partisan strife is that most want compromise from the government in Washington.

articles.author: Thomas Frank
articles.title: Civil engineers say fixing infrastructure will take $4.6 trillion
articles.description: Society's cost estimates are higher than estimates that federal agencies and other trade groups have made of infrastructure needs, CNN found.

articles.author: Tami Luhby
articles.title: What CBO got right - and wrong - on Obamacare
articles.description: CBO overestimated how many people would be covered on the individual exchanges, but was closer to the mark on how many Americans would be insured.

articles.author: Rene Marsh and Gregory Wallace, CNN
articles.title: Advocates call foul on CDC cuts in GOP Obamacare repeal bill
articles.description: Public health advocates are warning lawmakers the GOP plan to repeal Obamacare will eliminate nearly $1 billion in Centers for Disease Control and Prevention funding used for programs like preventing disease outbreaks and childhood lead poisoning.
